'livestreaming a mass murder in New Zealand' ) %].</p>


<p>And it's not stopping, though Facebook is belatedly responding. They take
down the livestreams of the [%
Ovid.cite('https://www.thesun.co.uk/news/2709224/two-afghan-migrants-revealed-as-those-arrested-over-horrific-three-hour-rape-streamed-on-facebook-live-in-sweden/',
'regular rapes') %], the [%
Ovid.cite('https://medium.com/@fatimaalmahmoud/gang-rape-on-facebook-live-why-did-facebook-not-interrupt-the-broadcast-9cc72275c3aa',
'gang rapes') %], the [%
Ovid.cite('https://www.huffpost.com/entry/facebook-live-sexual-assault_n_58d431aae4b03787d3567e1d',
'child rapes' ) %], the [%
Ovid.cite('https://www.thesun.co.uk/news/3426352/facebook-live-clips-murder-suicide-shootings-report/',
'murders and suicides') %], and more. This is somewhat better than in 2016
when [%
Ovid.cite('https://money.cnn.com/2016/06/17/technology/facebook-live-shooting-death/index.html',
'Facebook refused to remove the livestream of a murder because "it
doesn&rsquo;t violate the company&rsquo;s community standards"') %]. </p>

<p>And before we go any further, just ask yourself one question: how can a
company get so wrong that they think livestreaming murders isn't violating
"community standards"?</p>

<h2>The Opportunity</h2>

<p>Let's see if we can figure this out. Facebook has [%
Ovid.cite('https://www.statista.com/statistics/264810/number-of-monthly-active-facebook-users-worldwide/',
'2.3 billion monthly active users') %], millions of whom want anything else,
and [%
Ovid.cite('https://medium.com/utopiapress/facebook-lost-15-million-users-in-the-united-states-since-2017-705155060c4f',
'15 million of their most valuable customers have walked away since 2017' )
%]. Despite this, Facebook still basked in [%
Ovid.cite('https://www.statista.com/statistics/223289/facebooks-quarterly-net-income/',
'almost seven billion dollars in net income for the final quarter of 2018')%].
You would think that investors would be drooling at this. Millions of Facebook
high-value customers are <em>begging</em> for a new market! Even more
interesingly, there's little barrier to entry into this market.[%
Ovid.add_note('With the caveat that, as we see later in this article, many
competitors failed because their software wasn&lsquo;t up to the task. People
keep underestimating what it takes to build software on this scale.') %]
Taking a percentage of Facebook's market share is a huge business opportunity
but investors don&rsquo;t seem to be biting. Why is that? And can it be
changed?</p>

